# Regression test: BNG2.pl accepts `sign` as a user parameter name (it
# is not in BNG2.pl's %functions at bionetgen/bng2/Perl2/Expression.pm
# lines 56-96), but bngsim's init_builtins() registers `sign` as an
# ExprTk function alias for `sgn`. Pre-fix, define_variable("sign", ...)
# would fail at registration with a confusing "duplicate name" error.
# Post-fix, `sign` is in is_exprtk_reserved()'s mangling set, so the
# user's parameter is registered under the mangled key `r_sign` and
# expression rewriting handles the rest.
#
# Model: A --sign--> 0  (sign==1 here, so A(t) = 10*exp(-t))
begin parameters
    1 sign 1.0  # Constant
end parameters
begin species
    1 A() 10
end species
begin reactions
    1 1 0 sign #_R1
end reactions
begin groups
    1 A_tot  1
end groups
